<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1208896>
    dc:description "FIGURES 51–60. Tuberaleyrodes glutae (Corbett), microphotographs, puparium, dorsal and ventral views, 51, long first abdominal setae, median tubercles absent; 52, small first abdominal setae, vasiform orifice slightly elongate; 53, cephalothorax pattern of tuberculation; 54, abdomen, tubercles; 55, median tubercles; 56, vasiform orifice and caudal furrow; 57, thoracic tracheal pore; 58, submedian tubercles; 59, reduced number of median tubercles; 60, vasiform orifice." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1208896/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

